To describe stroke-related mortality and incidence, we used absolute and relative frequencies; and also 95% confidence intervals (95% CI). To estimate trend of stroke-related mortality and incidence, we used linear regression, estimating the slope (β), its respective probability (p), and the model's predictive ability (r2): The regression model used [15] is described below:




y = β0+β1*x, being



y = Mortality or incidence of hospitalizations for stroke in Brazilians aged 15 to 49 years (per 100,000 Brazilians aged 15 to 49 years);
